        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 2:27PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 226 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles east of Three Rivers, moving west at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Three Rivers, San Patricio, and Three Rivers Petroglyph Site.

This includes Highway 54 in New Mexico between mile markers 83 and
100.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
